│ My previous attempts to locate the buggy code with `grep` failed because my initial assumptions about the file location and function visibility were incorrect. After dumping the entire │
│ content of `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp` and manually inspecting it, I have finally located the source of the miscompilation.                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The problematic logic is in a `static` function named `tryToCombineTwoLoads` within `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp`. This function is called from `visitOr`    │
│ and is responsible for combining two `zext(load)` operations into a single wider load. The comment above the function perfectly describes the optimization pattern from the bug report.  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The bug itself is exactly what I first suspected: the code uses `getGEPInductionOperand` to extract the base pointer and offset from the load addresses. This older API is likely        │
│ mishandling the large 64-bit GEP offsets in the reproducer, causing them to be truncated and leading to an incorrect address calculation in the combined load.                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fix is to replace the calls to `getGEPInductionOperand` with the more modern and robust `getPointerInfo` API. This will ensure that the 64-bit offsets are handled correctly. I will │
│ construct a single `sed` command with multiple expressions to perform this replacement, targeting the correct file this time.                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The changes are:                                                                                                                                                                         │
